            Critically, GM3 is highly expressed in the <strong>spiral ganglion</strong> ‚Äî the neurons 
            of the auditory nerve (CN VIII). This creates a direct pathway for antigen uptake and 
            transport to the brainstem, paralleling the narcolepsy mechanism.
          </p>
