          <li>Matches the temporal and geographic clustering</li>
          <li>Could be investigated with existing medical records and samples</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="key-concept mt-8">
          <div class="key-concept-title">The Broader Lesson</div>
          <p class="mb-0">
            Whether or not this hypothesis is correct, it illustrates a crucial point: 
            <strong>gangliosides are a hidden system</strong> that determines which cells are 
            vulnerable to pathogens, toxins, and immune responses. Different influenza strains 
            target different gangliosides, potentially causing completely different diseases. 
            This "glycosphingolipid code" deserves far more attention in clinical medicine.
          </p>
        </div>

